Definition: a primitive root; to despond; causatively, to deject; broken, be grieved, make sad.

or כָּבֵד; a primitive root; to be heavy, i.e. in a bad sense (burdensome, severe, dull) or in a good sense (numerous, rich, honorable); causatively, to make weighty (in the same two senses); abounding with, more grievously afflict, boast, be chargeable, × be dim, glorify, be (make) glorious (things), glory, (very) great, be grievous, harden, be (make) heavy, be heavier, lay heavily, (bring to, come to, do, get, be had in) honour (self), (be) honourable (man), lade, × more be laid, make self many, nobles, prevail, promote (to honour), be rich, be (go) sore, stop.
a primitive root; properly, to feel pain; by implication, to grieve; figuratively, to spoil; grieving, mar, have pain, make sad (sore), (be) sorrowful.
from {{h3510}}; suffering (physical or mental), adversity; grief, pain, sorrow.
the same as {{h3515}}; the liver (as the heaviest of the viscera); liver.
feminine of {{h3515}}; difficulty; × heavily.
from {{h3513}}; weight, multitude, vehemence; grievousness, heavy, great number.
from {{h3513}}; heavy; figuratively in a good sense (numerous) or in a bad sense (severe, difficult, stupid); (so) great, grievous, hard(-ened), (too) heavy(-ier), laden, much, slow, sore, thick.
a primitive root; to expire or (causatively) to extinguish (fire, light, anger); go (put) out, quench.
rarely כָּבֹד; from {{h3513}}; properly, weight, but only figuratively in a good sense, splendor or copiousness; glorious(-ly), glory, honour(-able).
from the same as {{h3558}}; a cluster of stars, i.e. the Pleiades; Pleiades, seven stars.
a form for {{h3563}}; a cup; also a bag for money or weights; bag, cup, purse.
the same as {{h3591}}; Kidon, a place in Palestine; Chidon.
of uncertain derivation; perhaps tumult; battle.
from the same as {{h3589}} (compare {{h3539}}); properly, something struck off, i.e. a spark (as struck); spark.
from the same as {{h3589}}; (perhaps smaller than {{h2595}}); properly, something to strike with, i.e. a dart; lance, shield, spear, target.
or כֵּלַי; from {{h3557}} in the sense of withholding; niggardly; churl.
from an unused root meaning to clap or strike with noise; a club or sledge-hammer; hammer.
from {{h3559}}; properly, a statue, i.e. idol; but used (by euphemism) for some heathen deity (perhaps corresponding to Priapus or Baal-peor); Chiun.

or כִּיֹּר; from the same as {{h3564}}; properly, something round (as excavated or bored), i.e. a chafing-dish for coals or a caldron for cooking; hence (from similarity of form) a washbowl; also (for the same reason) a pulpit or platform; hearth, laver, pan, scaffold.
the same as {{h3528}}; length; Kebar, a river of Mesopotamia; Chebar. Compare {{h2249}}.
from {{h3527}}; properly, extent of time, i.e. a great while; hence, long ago, formerly, hitherto; already, (seeing that which), now.
a primitive root; properly, to plait together, i.e. (figuratively) to augment (especially in number or quantity, to accumulate); in abundance, multiply.
a primitive root; to trample; hence, to wash (properly, by stamping with the feet), whether literal (including the fulling process) or figurative; fuller, wash(-ing).
from an unused root meaning to twine or braid together; a fetter; fetter.
from {{h3527}}; vast, whether in extent (figuratively, of power, mighty; of time, aged), or in number, many; feeble, mighty, most, much, strong, valiant.
from {{h3527}} in the original sense of plaiting; a matrass (of intertwined materials); pillow.
from an unused root meaning to heap up; hilly; Cabon, a place in Palestine; Cabbon.
from the same as {{h3525}} in the sense of limitation; sterile; Cabul, the name of two places in Palestine; Cabul.
irregular feminine passive participle of {{h3513}}; weightiness, i.e. magnificence, wealth; carriage, all glorious, stately.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h3576}}; false; lying.
from the same as {{h3537}} in the sense of striking fire from a metal forged; a sparkling gem, probably the ruby; agate.
feminine of {{h3528}}; properly, length, i.e. a measure (of uncertain dimension); × little.
from {{h3527}} in its original sense; a sieve (as netted); sieve.
from an unused root meaning to dominate; a ram (just old enough to butt); lamb, sheep.
a primitive root; to tread down; hence, negatively, to disregard; positively, to conquer, subjugate, violate; bring into bondage, force, keep under, subdue, bring into subjection.
from {{h3533}}; a footstool (as trodden upon); footstool.
or כַּבְשָׂה; feminine of {{h3532}}; a ewe; (ewe) lamb.
from {{h3533}}; a smelting furnace (as reducing metals); furnace.
from an unused root meaning to deepen; properly, a pail; but generally of earthenware; a jar for domestic purposes; barrel, pitcher.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3548}}; priest.
active participle of {{h3547}}; literally one officiating, a priest; also (by courtesy) an acting priest (although a layman); chief ruler, × own, priest, prince, principal officer.
feminine of {{h3544}}; properly, a weakening; figuratively, alleviation, i.e. cure; healing.
from {{h3543}}; feeble, obscure; somewhat dark, darkish, wax dim, heaviness, smoking.

a primitive root, apparently meaning to mediate in religious services; but used only as denominative from {{h3548}}; to officiate as a priest; figuratively, to put on regalia; deck, be (do the office of a, execute the, minister in the) priest('s office).
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to and {{h3557}}; to be able; be able, could.

from the prefix k and {{h1931}}; properly, like this, i.e. by implication, (of manner) thus (or so); also (of place) here (or hither); or (of time) now; also, here,   hitherto, like, on the other side, so (and much), such, on that manner, (on) this (manner, side, way, way and that way),   mean while, yonder.
of foreign origin; Kedorlaomer, an early Persian king; Chedorlaomer.
a primitive root; to be weak, i.e. (figuratively) to despond (causatively, rebuke), or (of light, the eye) to grow dull; darken, be dim, fail, faint, restrain, × utterly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3541}}; hitherto.
from an unused root meaning to store away; a jewel (probably gold beads); tablet.

a primitive root; properly, to be erect (i.e. stand perpendicular); hence (causatively) to set up, in a great variety of applications, whether literal (establish, fix, prepare, apply), or figurative (appoint, render sure, proper or prosperous); certain(-ty), confirm, direct, faithfulness, fashion, fasten, firm, be fitted, be fixed, frame, be meet, ordain, order, perfect, (make) preparation, prepare (self), provide, make provision, (be, make) ready, right, set (aright, fast, forth), be stable, (e-) stablish, stand, tarry, × very deed.
probably from the same as {{h3522}} (in the sense of rolling) or {{h3554}} (in the sense of blazing); a star (as round or as shining); figuratively, a prince; star(-gazer).

a primitive root; properly, to keep in; hence, to measure; figuratively, to maintain (in various senses); (be able to, can) abide, bear, comprehend, contain, feed, forbearing, guide, hold(-ing in), nourish(-er), be present, make provision, receive, sustain, provide sustenance (victuals).
a primitive root; properly, to prick or penetrate; hence, to blister (as smarting or eating into); burn.
from {{h3554}}; a branding; burning.
of foreign derivation; Kub, a country near Egypt; Chub.
from an unused root meaning to be high or rounded; a helmet (as arched); helmet. Compare {{h6959}}.
from {{h3547}}; priesthood; priesthood, priest's office.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h3854}} in the sense of piercing; a window (as a perforation); window.
patronymically from {{h3568}}; a Cushite, or descendant of Cush; Cushi, Cushite, Ethiopian(-s).
probably of foreign origin; Cush (or Ethiopia), the name of a son of Ham, and of his territory; also of an Israelite; Chush, Cush, Ethiopia.

from an unused root meaning to hold together; a cup (as a container), often figuratively, a lot (as if a potion); also some unclean bird, probably an owl (perhaps from the cup-like cavity of its eye); cup, (small) owl. Compare {{h3599}}.
from {{h3559}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has sustained; Conanjah, the name of two Israelites; Conaniah, Cononiah. Compare {{h3663}}.
from {{h3559}}; something prepared, i.e. a sacrificial wafer; cake.
probably from {{h3559}}; established; Kun, a place in Syria; Chun.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3566}}; Cyrus.
or (Ezra 1:1 (last time),2) כֹּרֶשׁ; from the Persian; Koresh (or Cyrus), the Persian king; Cyrus.
from {{h3564}} and {{h6227}}; furnace of smoke; Cor-Ashan, a place in Palestine; Chorashan.
from an unused root meaning properly, to dig through; a pot or furnace (as if excavated); furnace. Compare {{h3600}}.
from {{h3787}}; prosperity; in plural freedom; × chain.
or (feminine) כּוּתָה; of foreign origin; Cuth or Cuthah, a province of Assyria; Cuth.
a primitive root; to lie (i.e. deceive), literally or figuratively; fail, (be found a, make a) liar, lie, lying, be in vain.
from {{h3576}}; falsehood; literally (untruth) or figuratively (idol); deceitful, false, leasing,   liar, lie, lying.
the same as {{h3569}}; Cushi, the name of two Israelites; Cushi.
feminine of {{h3569}}; a Cushite woman; Ethiopian.
perhaps from {{h3568}}; Cushan, a region of Arabia; Cushan.
apparently from {{h3572}} and the dual of {{h7564}}; Cushan of double wickedness; Cushan-Rishathajim, a Mesopotamian king; Chushan-rishathayim.
from {{h3576}}; fallacious; Cozeba, a place in Palestine; Choseba.
from {{h3576}}; false; Cozbi, a Midianitess; Cozbi.
a form for {{h3564}} (only in the dual); a cooking range (consisting of two parallel stones, across which the boiler is set); ranges for pots.
by variation for {{h3502}}; Jithra, an Israelite (or Ishmaelite); Ithra.
from {{h3499}} with pron. suffix; his excellence; Jethro, Moses' father-in-law; Jethro. Compare {{h3500}}.
feminine of {{h3499}}; properly, excellence, i.e. (by implication) wealth; abundance, riches.
patronymically from {{h3500}}; a Jithrite or descendant of Jether; Ithrite.
from {{h3498}}; preeminence, gain; better, excellency(-leth), profit(-able).
from {{h3499}} and {{h5971}}; excellence of people; Jithream, a son of David; Ithream.
from {{h3498}}; excellent; Jithran, the name of an Edomite and of an Israelite; Ithran.
of uncertain derivation; Jetheth, an Edomite; Jetheth.
feminine active participle of {{h3498}}; the lobe or flap of the liver (as if redundant or outhanging); caul.
from a primitive root meaning to strike; a crushing; figuratively, calamity; destruction.

a primitive particle (the full form of the prepositional prefix) indicating causal relations of all kinds, antecedent or consequent; (by implication) very widely used as a relative conjunction or adverb (as below); often largely modified by other particles annexed; and,   (forasmuch, inasmuch, where-) as, assured(-ly),   but, certainly, doubtless,   else, even,   except, for, how, (because, in, so, than) that,   nevertheless, now, rightly, seeing, since, surely, then, therefore,   (al-) though,   till, truly,   until, when, whether, while, whom, yea, yet.

or (Daniel 11:6) כּוֹחַ; from an unused root meaning to be firm; vigor, literally (force, in a good or a bad sense) or figuratively (capacity, means, produce); also (from its hardiness) a large lizard; ability, able, chameleon, force, fruits, might, power(-ful), strength, substance, wealth.
from {{h3576}}; falsified; Kezib, a place in Palestine; Chezib.
a primitive root; to paint (with stibium); paint.
a primitive root; to secrete, by act or word; hence (intensively) to destroy; conceal, cut down (off), desolate, hide.
from {{h3584}}; literally a failure of flesh, i.e. emaciation; figuratively, hypocrisy; leanness, lies, lying.
a primitive root; to be untrue, in word (to lie, feign, disown) or deed (to disappoint, fail, cringe); deceive, deny, dissemble, fail, deal falsely, be found liars, (be-) lie, lying, submit selves.
from {{h3554}}; a brand or scar; burning.
from {{h3584}}; faithless; lying.
